The current Flash installer script (version 9,0,31,0) has a bug insofar as it checks for the superuser by checking for the ''user name'' "root", not for the ''user id'' "0". This is obviously a problem in GoboLinux, where the superuser is named "gobo", not "root".

The following lines are <font color="red">''incorrect''</font>:

<div style="background-color: #DDDDDD; font-family: monospace">ROOTINSTALL=0<br />
<br />
<nowiki># check user</nowiki><br />
USERID=`id | sed -e 's/<font color="red">)</font>.*//; s/^.*<font color="red">(</font>//;'`<br />
if [ "X$USERID" = "X<font color="red">root</font>" ]; then
:ROOTINSTALL=1
fi</div>

The following lines are correct:

<div style="background-color: #DDDDDD; font-family: monospace">ROOTINSTALL=0<br />
<br />
<nowiki># check user</nowiki><br />
USERID=`id | sed -e 's/<font color="blue">(</font>.*//; s/^.*<font color="blue">=</font>//;'`<br />
if [ "X$USERID" = "X<font color="blue">0</font>" ]; then
:ROOTINSTALL=1
fi</div>

I have notified Adobe but it doesn't hurt watching if they actually fix that.

